## 2026-07-04 (cont'd) — Tier 3

- Tier 3 Wave 1 (Tasks 3A/3B/3C — core loop, Zotero, CSV export
  endpoints): DONE, merged. Task 3A took 5 verification rounds (largest
  task): cross-session isolation gaps across search/queue/saved/
  decisions, a non-round-trip cache test, and Paper.retracted computed
  but never exposed in any API response were all found and fixed.
  Task 3B: fixed a narrow session-fixation-adjacent atomicity bug
  (connection insert and session rotation were two separate commits).
  Task 3C: fixed a formula-injection bypass via leading whitespace/
  invisible Unicode characters. Also resolved the open SPEC §10.4 gap
  by adding DELETE /zotero/connection.
- Tier 3 Wave 2 (Task 3D, cross-cutting middleware): DONE, merged.
  Adversarial review found a real BLOCKING issue — the inbound rate
  limiter was trivially bypassable (keyed on session_id, but a fresh
  cookie-less request gets a fresh session, so the limit never
  engaged). Fixed by making client IP the primary key. Both tester and
  adversarial independently re-attempted the original attack against
  the fix before confirming it closed, and adversarial ruled out an
  X-Forwarded-For spoofing bypass too.
- Tier 3 is now FULLY CLOSED. Every task this tier was independently
  verified by tester and adversarial-generalist; every real finding
  was fixed and re-verified by reproducing the underlying defect first
  (revert, confirm failure, restore, confirm fix) rather than trusting
